---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Flow Health Monitor | Email Pulse - AI Agent for Klaviyo"
  description="The Flow Health Monitor audits every Klaviyo flow in your account, classifies each one by real incremental impact, and delivers prioritized tasks to your team — automatically."
>
  <!-- Google Fonts: Inter (demo-specific) -->
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
    slot="head"
  />

  <div class="fhm-demo">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="fhm-hero">
      <div class="fhm-container">
        <div class="fhm-badge">AI Agent for Klaviyo</div>
        <h1 class="fhm-h1">Your flows are either making money or wasting it.<br />This agent tells you which.</h1>
        <p class="fhm-lead">The Flow Health Monitor audits every Klaviyo flow in your account, classifies each one by real incremental impact, and delivers prioritized tasks to your team &mdash; automatically.</p>
        <div class="fhm-cta-row">
          <a href="#" class="fhm-cta-primary">Start Free &rarr;</a>
          <a href="#how-it-works" class="fhm-cta-secondary">See how it works</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Problem Section -->
    <section class="fhm-section">
      <div class="fhm-container">
        <h2 class="fhm-h2">You already have the data. The problem is what to do with it.</h2>
        <p class="fhm-body">Klaviyo dashboards show you open rates, click rates, revenue per recipient. But they don&rsquo;t tell you what any of it <em>means</em> for a specific flow &mdash; or what to do next.</p>
        <p class="fhm-body" style="margin-top:16px">You can connect Claude to Klaviyo&rsquo;s MCP and ask it to audit your flows. But here&rsquo;s what actually happens:</p>
        <div class="fhm-versus">
          <div class="fhm-versus-card fhm-bad">
            <div class="fhm-versus-label">What Claude says Monday</div>
            <code>Your Browse Abandonment flow shows
strong engagement. Open rate of 38%
is healthy. Consider A/B testing
subject lines for improvement.</code>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-versus-card fhm-good">
            <div class="fhm-versus-label">What Claude says Wednesday</div>
            <code>Your Browse Abandonment flow is
underperforming. At 38% open rate
and 0.3% conversion, this flow
needs significant restructuring.</code>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:24px" class="fhm-small">Same flow. Same data. Different answer. LLMs interpret numbers probabilistically &mdash; they don&rsquo;t have fixed rules for what &ldquo;good&rdquo; or &ldquo;bad&rdquo; means in your account. The Flow Health Monitor fixes this with deterministic classification that produces the same answer every time.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Classification Section -->
    <section class="fhm-section">
      <div class="fhm-container">
        <h2 class="fhm-h2">Every flow gets classified. No ambiguity.</h2>
        <p class="fhm-body">Instead of generic benchmarks, the agent uses <strong>uplift modeling</strong> &mdash; comparing shoppers influenced by each flow against those who weren&rsquo;t &mdash; to measure true incremental impact. Every flow lands in one of four categories:</p>
        <div class="fhm-classification-grid">
          <div class="fhm-class-card fhm-sureshot">
            <span class="fhm-tag">Sure Shot</span>
            <h3 class="fhm-h3">Protect it</h3>
            <p class="fhm-body">High engagement lift + high revenue lift. This flow is generating real incremental value. Document what works. Don&rsquo;t touch it unnecessarily.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-class-card fhm-persuadable">
            <span class="fhm-tag">Persuadable</span>
            <h3 class="fhm-h3">Optimize it</h3>
            <p class="fhm-body">Engagement is there but revenue isn&rsquo;t following. Or vice versa. This is your highest-ROI optimization opportunity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-class-card fhm-sleeping">
            <span class="fhm-tag">Sleeping Dog</span>
            <h3 class="fhm-h3">Leave it alone</h3>
            <p class="fhm-body">Low engagement, but still converting the people it reaches. Tweaking this will likely hurt more than help. Monitor, don&rsquo;t optimize.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-class-card fhm-lostcause">
            <span class="fhm-tag">Lost Cause</span>
            <h3 class="fhm-h3">Fix it or kill it</h3>
            <p class="fhm-body">Low engagement. Low revenue lift. This flow is consuming resources without generating incremental value. Pause, redesign, or remove.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Output Table Section -->
    <section class="fhm-section" id="how-it-works">
      <div class="fhm-container-wide">
        <h2 class="fhm-h2">Here&rsquo;s what the agent actually produces.</h2>
        <p class="fhm-body">For an account with 8 active flows, a single run generates a complete audit with prioritized actions:</p>
        <div class="fhm-table-wrap">
          <table class="fhm-output-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Flow</th>
                <th>Classification</th>
                <th>Priority</th>
                <th>Action</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Abandoned Cart</strong></td>
                <td><span class="fhm-tag-inline fhm-tag-green">Sure Shot</span></td>
                <td>Protect</td>
                <td>Generating $4.82 RPR with 12% placed order rate. Document success factors. Consider scaling to SMS.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Welcome Series</strong></td>
                <td><span class="fhm-tag-inline fhm-tag-blue">Persuadable</span></td>
                <td>Optimize</td>
                <td>Strong opens (52%) but low conversion (1.8%). Test stronger first-purchase incentive in email 2.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Post-Purchase</strong></td>
                <td><span class="fhm-tag-inline fhm-tag-blue">Persuadable</span></td>
                <td>Optimize</td>
                <td>Cross-sell timing is off. Move product rec from day 3 to day 7 based on average fulfillment window.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>VIP Repeat</strong></td>
                <td><span class="fhm-tag-inline fhm-tag-amber">Sleeping Dog</span></td>
                <td>Monitor</td>
                <td>Low open rate (18%) but $4.20 RPR. This audience buys regardless. Don&rsquo;t over-optimize.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Browse Abandonment</strong></td>
                <td><span class="fhm-tag-inline fhm-tag-red">Lost Cause</span></td>
                <td>Fix / Kill</td>
                <td>12% open, 0.3% conversion, no measurable revenue lift. Pause and redesign with better product targeting.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Winback</strong></td>
                <td><span class="fhm-tag-inline fhm-tag-red">Lost Cause</span></td>
                <td>Fix / Kill</td>
                <td>Sending to 120-day lapsed with generic content. Segment by last purchase category or sunset.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:20px" class="fhm-small">Each row becomes a task in your project management tool (Asana, Slack, or your CRM) with the classification as a tag, the priority level, and the specific recommendation as the task description. Your team opens their board Monday morning and knows exactly what to work on.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Steps Section -->
    <section class="fhm-section">
      <div class="fhm-container">
        <h2 class="fhm-h2">Six steps. Fully automated.</h2>
        <div class="fhm-steps">
          <div class="fhm-step">
            <div class="fhm-step-number">1</div>
            <div class="fhm-step-content">
              <h3 class="fhm-h3">Pull flow data</h3>
              <p class="fhm-body">The agent calls Email Pulse&rsquo;s evaluation engine with your Klaviyo account, pulling metrics, setup quality scores, and performance scores for every active flow.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-step">
            <div class="fhm-step-number">2</div>
            <div class="fhm-step-content">
              <h3 class="fhm-h3">Classify each flow</h3>
              <p class="fhm-body">Deterministic logic applies the uplift matrix &mdash; engagement lift &times; monetization lift &mdash; to classify each flow as Sure Shot, Persuadable, Sleeping Dog, or Lost Cause. Same data, same answer, every time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-step">
            <div class="fhm-step-number">3</div>
            <div class="fhm-step-content">
              <h3 class="fhm-h3">Score setup quality</h3>
              <p class="fhm-body">Each flow is evaluated against completeness criteria: trigger configuration, message setup, timing logic, tracking, and status. Missing elements are flagged as quick wins.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-step">
            <div class="fhm-step-number">4</div>
            <div class="fhm-step-content">
              <h3 class="fhm-h3">Compare to flow-type benchmarks</h3>
              <p class="fhm-body">Performance is checked against flow-type-specific thresholds &mdash; not generic industry averages. An abandoned cart flow is held to a different standard than a winback flow.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-step">
            <div class="fhm-step-number">5</div>
            <div class="fhm-step-content">
              <h3 class="fhm-h3">Generate priorities</h3>
              <p class="fhm-body">Flows are tiered: Sure Shots to protect and Lost Causes to fix are Tier 1. Persuadables are Tier 2. Sleeping Dogs are Tier 3. Your team works top-down.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-step">
            <div class="fhm-step-number">6</div>
            <div class="fhm-step-content">
              <h3 class="fhm-h3">Deliver tasks</h3>
              <p class="fhm-body">Prioritized action items are pushed to Asana, Slack, or your CRM. Each task includes the classification, specific recommendation, and supporting data.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why Different Section -->
    <section class="fhm-section">
      <div class="fhm-container">
        <h2 class="fhm-h2">Why this isn&rsquo;t just another AI wrapper.</h2>
        <div class="fhm-problem-block">
          <p class="fhm-body"><strong>Most &ldquo;AI audit&rdquo; tools ask an LLM to look at your numbers and tell you what it thinks.</strong> That&rsquo;s a book report, not an audit. The output changes every time you run it. You can&rsquo;t automate on top of something unreliable.</p>
          <p class="fhm-body" style="margin-top:16px">The Flow Health Monitor uses a four-layer architecture: data comes in through Email Pulse&rsquo;s MCP, <em>code</em> applies the classification rules (not an LLM), AI generates the natural language explanations, and structured output pushes tasks to your tools. The interpretation is deterministic. The explanations are intelligent. That&rsquo;s the difference between a toy and a system.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Audience Section -->
    <section class="fhm-section">
      <div class="fhm-container">
        <h2 class="fhm-h2">Built for the people who actually manage flows.</h2>
        <div class="fhm-audience-grid">
          <div class="fhm-audience-card">
            <span class="fhm-emoji">&#127978;</span>
            <h3 class="fhm-h3">For brand teams</h3>
            <p class="fhm-body">You built your Klaviyo flows six months ago. Maybe a year. Some are working, some aren&rsquo;t, and you&rsquo;re not sure which. The agent gives you a clear, prioritized picture of what to fix &mdash; without hiring a consultant or spending a week in spreadsheets.</p>
            <p class="fhm-body" style="margin-top:12px">Connect your account, run the agent, get your audit. Setup takes minutes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="fhm-audience-card">
            <span class="fhm-emoji">&#127970;</span>
            <h3 class="fhm-h3">For agencies</h3>
            <p class="fhm-body">You manually audit flows for every client. Every month. It&rsquo;s the most time-consuming part of your retention work, and the output depends on who&rsquo;s doing the audit. The agent standardizes your methodology across every account, every analyst, every time.</p>
            <p class="fhm-body" style="margin-top:12px">Same classification framework. Same priority logic. Same task output. Scale your audits without scaling your headcount.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Banner -->
    <section class="fhm-section" style="border-top:none;padding-bottom:0">
      <div class="fhm-container-wide">
        <div class="fhm-cta-banner">
          <h2 class="fhm-h2" style="color:#fff;margin-bottom:12px">Stop guessing which flows need attention.</h2>
          <p class="fhm-body" style="color:#94a3b8;margin-bottom:32px">Connect your Klaviyo account and get your first automated flow audit in minutes. Free to start &mdash; no infrastructure, no setup complexity.</p>
          <a href="#" class="fhm-cta-banner-btn">Start Free &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer Note -->
    <div class="fhm-footer-note">
      <p class="fhm-small">Flow Health Monitor is powered by <a href="https://emailpulse.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="fhm-link">Email Pulse</a> &mdash; the AI intelligence layer for Klaviyo.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  /* =============================================
     Flow Health Monitor Demo — Scoped Styles
     All classes prefixed with fhm- to avoid
     conflicts with the site's global styles.
     ============================================= */

  .fhm-demo {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    color: #0f172a;
    line-height: 1.6;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  /* Containers */
  .fhm-container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
  .fhm-container-wide { max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }

  /* Sections */
  .fhm-section { padding: 80px 0; }
  .fhm-section + .fhm-section { border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0; }

  /* Typography */
  .fhm-h1 {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .fhm-h2 {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .fhm-h3 {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .fhm-body {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: #334155;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .fhm-lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #334155;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .fhm-small {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #64748b;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .fhm-hero {
    padding: 100px 0 80px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }
  .fhm-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #6366f1;
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  /* CTAs */
  .fhm-cta-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .fhm-cta-primary {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    background: #6366f1;
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 14px 28px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .fhm-cta-primary:hover { background: #4f46e5; }
  .fhm-cta-secondary {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    color: #334155;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 14px 28px;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .fhm-cta-secondary:hover { color: #0f172a; }

  /* Versus Cards */
  .fhm-versus { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .fhm-versus-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; border: 1px solid; }
  .fhm-versus-card.fhm-bad { background: #fef2f2; border-color: #fecaca; }
  .fhm-versus-card.fhm-good { background: #ecfdf5; border-color: #a7f3d0; }
  .fhm-versus-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .fhm-versus-card.fhm-bad .fhm-versus-label { color: #ef4444; }
  .fhm-versus-card.fhm-good .fhm-versus-label { color: #10b981; }
  .fhm-versus-card code {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #334155;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
  }

  /* Classification Grid */
  .fhm-classification-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .fhm-class-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; border: 1px solid; }
  .fhm-class-card .fhm-h3 { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .fhm-class-card .fhm-body { font-size: 0.9375rem; }
  .fhm-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .fhm-sureshot { background: #ecfdf5; border-color: #a7f3d0; }
  .fhm-sureshot .fhm-tag { background: #10b981; }
  .fhm-persuadable { background: #eff6ff; border-color: #bfdbfe; }
  .fhm-persuadable .fhm-tag { background: #3b82f6; }
  .fhm-sleeping { background: #fffbeb; border-color: #fde68a; }
  .fhm-sleeping .fhm-tag { background: #f59e0b; }
  .fhm-lostcause { background: #fef2f2; border-color: #fecaca; }
  .fhm-lostcause .fhm-tag { background: #ef4444; }

  /* Output Table */
  .fhm-table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; margin-top: 32px; }
  .fhm-output-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }
  .fhm-output-table thead { background: #0f172a; }
  .fhm-output-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .fhm-output-table td {
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    color: #334155;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .fhm-output-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .fhm-tag-inline {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: #fff;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .fhm-tag-green { background: #10b981; }
  .fhm-tag-blue { background: #3b82f6; }
  .fhm-tag-amber { background: #f59e0b; }
  .fhm-tag-red { background: #ef4444; }

  /* Steps */
  .fhm-steps { margin-top: 32px; }
  .fhm-step { display: flex; gap: 20px; padding: 24px 0; }
  .fhm-step + .fhm-step { border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0; }
  .fhm-step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #6366f1;
  }
  .fhm-step-content .fhm-h3 { margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .fhm-step-content .fhm-body { font-size: 0.9375rem; }

  /* Audience Grid */
  .fhm-audience-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .fhm-audience-card {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px;
  }
  .fhm-emoji { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 12px; display: block; }
  .fhm-audience-card .fhm-body { font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-top: 8px; }

  /* Problem Block */
  .fhm-problem-block {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  /* CTA Banner */
  .fhm-cta-banner {
    background: #0f172a;
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 48px;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .fhm-cta-banner-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    background: #fff;
    color: #0f172a;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 14px 28px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .fhm-cta-banner-btn:hover { background: #f1f5f9; }

  /* Footer Note */
  .fhm-footer-note {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 40px 0 60px;
    border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }
  .fhm-link { color: #6366f1; text-decoration: none; }
  .fhm-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .fhm-versus,
    .fhm-classification-grid,
    .fhm-audience-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
